title: Brighton and Hove Albion vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2024/2025
description: Having lost four of their first five Premier League home games against Liverpool, Brighton are now unbeaten in their last two against the Reds at the Amex Stadium in the competition. Liverpool have won their last two Premier League games against Brighton, having won just one of their previous seven against the Seagulls beforehand.

title: Everton vs. Southampton - English Premier League 2024/2025
description: Everton lost their last home league match against Southampton in January 2023, ending a 17-game unbeaten run against Saints at Goodison Park. They last lost consecutive home league games against them in April 1974. Following their 1-0 win at St Mary’s in the reverse fixture, Southampton are looking to complete the league double over Everton for the first time since 1997-98.

description: Arsenal have lost just one of their last 20 Premier League home games against Newcastle, winning 11 of the last 12 since a 1-0 loss in November 2010. title: Nantes vs Montpellier - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: Nantes have won 64.3% of their Ligue 1 home games against Montpellier in the 21st century, their highest success rate against an opponent they have faced 10+ times on home soil during this period. description: Lens will face Monaco in Ligue 1 for the 108th time, the team that RCL have faced the most in the top-flight but also the one against which they have lost the most, with two defeats in the last three meetings. Lens are unbeaten in their last five matches to finish a Ligue 1 season, two of which came against Monaco. This is the third time in the last five years that the two teams have faced each other at Lens to close their season.

title: Lille vs Reims - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: Lille have won two games in a row against Reims in Ligue 1, after failing to win any of the previous four. LOSC could string together three wins against Reims for the second time in their top-flight history, after August 2020-September 2021. Reims have conceded at least one goal in each of their last 13 away games against Lille in Ligue 1, the longest run of its kind for SdR against a current top-flight team.

title: Olympique Marseille vs Rennes - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34

Marseille have finished just one of the last 12 Ligue 1 seasons with a defeat, losing 1-0 at Ajaccio on 3 June 2023.

title: Strasbourg vs Le Havre - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: The 39 meetings between Strasbourg and Le Havre in Ligue 1 have produced only three draws, a ratio of 7.7%. This is the lowest percentage of draws between two Ligue 1 teams among those who have faced each other 20+ times. Strasbourg have lost their last three matches to finish a Ligue 1 season, but they have been away from home each time, at Marseille, Lorient and Lyon in the last three years. At home, RCSA have gone three games to close a season without losing.

title: Borussia Dortmund vs Holstein Kiel - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: Holstein Kiel and Borussia Dortmund have met three times so far: BVB won 4-0 away in the quarter-finals of the 2011/12 DFB-Pokal and then 5-0 at home in the semi-finals in 2020/21, before the Storks won 4-2 in this season’s reverse fixture. It was Dortmund’s first defeat against a Bundesliga debutant since August 2019. Borussia Dortmund have won four Bundesliga games in a row for the first time since March 2024. They have picked up 19 of a possible 21 points from the last seven matchdays, a league high.

title: Mainz 05 vs Bayer Leverkusen - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: 1. FSV Mainz 05 have lost 11 of their 14 Bundesliga games against Bayer 04 Leverkusen since the start of 2018 – the Werkself haven’t beaten any other side more often during this period and the 05ers haven’t suffered more defeats against any other side. Leverkusen have won each of the last three meetings. Bayer 04 Leverkusen have only won one of their last five Bundesliga games. 68 points from 33 games is still their third-best record in the top flight. Last weekend’s 4-2 defeat against Borussia Dortmund saw them concede more than three goals in a Bundesliga game for the first time since October 2022.

description: The German Bundesliga is live and exclusive only on beIN. The 2024–25 Bundesliga will be the 62nd season of the Bundesliga. The league comprises of 18 teams 16 of which competed in the league campaign during the previous season, while the remaining two were promoted from Bundesliga 2.

title: Freiburg vs Eintracht Frankfurt - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: This fixture is SC Freiburg’s 850th Bundesliga match. They have only won one of their last 10 top-flight meetings with Eintracht Frankfurt and are winless in their last five, their longest ever wait for victory against the Eagles. SC Freiburg have picked up 13 of a possible 15 points over the last five matchdays, a joint league high together with Borussia Dortmund. Eintracht Frankfurt have also remained unbeaten during this period, conceding the joint-fewest goals in the league.

title: Heidenheim vs Werder Bremen - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: Werder Bremen and 1. FC Heidenheim have met three times in the Bundesliga and Werder are still yet to win. Of teams currently in the top flight, Heidenheim have only otherwise picked up points in every Bundesliga meeting with Union Berlin. 1. FC Heidenheim will finish no lower than 16th and are three points and six goals adrift of 15th place – since three points per win was introduced, only Borussia Monchengladbach in 1997/98 and VfB Stuttgart in 2021/22 have ever made up a three-point deficit to 15th on the final matchday.
